sentences: Ummu Syaikhah Stacy binti Anam (born 18 August 1990), known professionally as Stacy, is a Malaysian singer, composer, songwriter who rose to fame after winning the sixth season of Akademi Fantasia, receiving 43% of over 3.8 million votes.
Her debut album, Aku Stacy, was released on 9 March 2009.
She studied in diploma of music and art, and began her first semester in February 2010.
In the meantime, her first compilation live album, The Best of Stacy was released in September 2008 which featured all of her ten performances in Akademi Fantasia, excluding the fifth concert.

In December 2008, the song "Aku Stacy" made it to the final round of Anugerah Juara Lagu, an annual award show in Malaysia to honour the best Malay song every year, a rare accomplishment made by newcomers in the industry.
Along with Nubhan, fellow student of AF6, Stacy was listed fourth in Murai's list of "Most Outstanding Newcomers of 2008".

In February 2009, Stacy was short-listed as the top 5 finalist for three major categories in Anugerah Bintang Popular, namely Most Popular Artiste, Most Popular Female New Artist, as well as Most Popular Female Singer, where she was voted as the Most Popular Female New Artist.
Her debut album, Aku Stacy, was released on 9 March 2009.
Stacy's third single, "Pakai Buang" was released on 9 May 2009.
In June 2009, Stacy was nominated in Shout!
Awards 2009 for the category of Popstar Award, in which she won.

She was also being nominated in two categories of 2009 Anugerah Planet Muzik, which are Best Vocal Performance in a Song for New Female Artiste as well as Most Popular Malaysian Artiste which was won by Siti Nurhaliza by only 1%.
In March 2011, Stacy participated in Astro Mania! contest where Malaysia's established singers compete amongst themselves to be crowned the Superstar.
Her second album, entitled Stay-C was released on 9 September 2011.
On 11 November 2011, Stacy's new single "Kasanova" was officially launched with behind the scenes footage, special acoustics performances and the world premiere of Kasanova music video.
The song was also hailed at No.2 as the most popular song in Malaysia in 2012.
The video was released in July 2012.
The success of her final single from Stay-C, "Bosan" is proven when the song managed to compete in the grand final of AJL28 in January 2014.
Stacy's third album, #1 was released on 17 May 2014 at Zouk KL.
Stacy proved herself once again as a consistent artist when her first single "Gilalah" made it to the final of AJL29 in 2015.
In September 2014, Stacy released the video of "Patah" a promotional single from the album.
The accompanying music video was released on 4 August 2015.
The song also brought Stacy to her 7th AJL appearance in January 2016.
It is confirmed that Stacy would release a new single entitled "Romeo" in December 2015.
The single was later released on 30 January 2016.
The song was released on Team Sangat Gila Stacy channel on YouTube on 22 October 2016.
After about a year hiatus, Stacy released her new dance-pop single titled "Cakap Ke Tangan" on 25 August 2017.

Stacy was previously a Roman Catholic Christian before embracing Islam in August 2015 to marry her love, and chose Ummu Syaikhah Stacy binti Anam as her Muslim name.
Stacy married Malaysian singer-songwriter Akim Ahmad in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah in 2016.
On 17 February 2017, the couple welcomed their first child, a daughter named Eshaal.
In 2013, she was appointed as Drive M7 (an energy drink) ambassador, together with Aaron Aziz and Fizo Omar.
Stacy was a spokesperson for BOH Tea (2009), Power Root-Ali Cafe (2009), Canon Malaysia (2009) and Corntoz Mamee Double-Decker (2009).
Since 2017, Stacy is one of the spokespersons for Anlene.
The judging panel often harbours her performances with praises every week for being consistent, which implied her as the front-runner of the season.
The song quickly became her first number one single in Carta Era for two weeks, as well as topping Carta 30 Era at number one.
It stayed in the chart for 22 weeks, making its own history as one of the songs that stayed in the chart for a long period of time.
The album was well-received as it sold thousand copies in the first week.

In December 2008, the song "Aku Stacy" made it to the final round of Anugerah Juara Lagu, an annual award show in Malaysia to honour the best Malay song every year, a rare accomplishment made by newcomers in the industry.
In Carta Muzik Muzik, "Pakai Buang" debuted at number 5 and is currently peaking at No. 4.
She remained at Top 5 every week in the competition until the finals.
Although she was sick a day before her performance, she wowed the audiences with her vocals and moves.
